# How To Take On Scrapbooking !!

*"Hey, Anna!* 

*I've always found scrapbooking to be such a fun way to express creativity, but I'm not sure where to start.*

*What recommendations would you have for **beginner scrapbookers?**"*

![random scrapbooker on Pinterest=](image.png)

Well, I'm not a university, but I have a couple months of scrapbooking experience under my belt, and I self-consider myself an expert. 

**Scrapbooking is different for everyone.** The *official* definition is, ["a book with empty pages where you can stick newspaper articles, pictures, etc. that you have collected and want to keep"](https://dictionary.cambridge.org/us/dictionary/english/scrapbook), according to Cambridge University. 

Officially *unofficially*, I'd say **it's anything you want to make it**-*buttt* that usually starts with a sketchbook and a magazine. 

**Just don't overthink it--the art comes from the mess you make of it.**

I sometimes make a theme for a page/notebook, or I just let it become something unexpected through mindless ripping. 

The photo you see above is from a search on Pinterest of scrapbooking--so, naturally, it comes up with the most aesthetic photo with the cutest nails with *probably* some use of AI. It's cute--but it's not me. But it may be more you than it is me! I'm not judging! (I'm judging).

**This is what scrapbooking is like to me.**

![messy scrapbook=](image-1.png)

Now, I won't throw myself completely under the bus--mine usually don't get that bad. *However*, there certaintly have been some pages SO bad that I had to throw them away before anyone saw them. You know it's bad when it blends right in with your trash as if it wasn't supposed to be art to begin with.

**You can fix this. You can steer clear of this mess.** You can do something I have yet to do but have heard from the ether that people do: [scrapbook bundles](https://www.etsy.com/search?q=scrapbook+supplies&ref=auto-1&as_prefix=scrapbook+) on Etsy. This is for you’re aiming for a certain aesthetic.

**Scrapbooking changes your way of thinking.** I once looked at trash, and thought, *"Oh, that's trash!"* Now I look at it, and go, *"Ooh, the potential!"* If you wish to have the same fate, keep reading, and I'm sorry.

